<br>
The three fine barbarian ladies in that room had, in fact, seen a goblin wizard, as they killed it right in front of me as I arrived. One of them guessed what I was about and told me it was my lucky day. I gave them all gnome-shaped cookies (hey, what else could I do for them? Buff them with See Invisibile?) and gated to the Nek forest for the run to the temple (I already had the other three parts in my pack).<br>
<br>
LOVE the Staff of Temperate Flux. Well worth the effort it takes to get in your late 20s. And it aggros like a son of a bitch, but the insta-cast allows me to begin (or complete) casting of an attack spell in the time the mob takes to reach me.<br>
<br>
Thanks for the advice, guys! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usaedyan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Saedyan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/2/01 2:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Got it.</span><hr size=1> When does this staff start being able to be right clicked? At what lvl.? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nezander>Nezander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/9/01 11:22 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Got it.</span><hr size=1> Whizbang - I'm working on this quest right now; have everything I need except both the 'hearts'. Any advice about finding the 'Hear of Fire'? (I assume your advice about the 'Heart of Ice' is to camp the preacher room - or /ooc there if it's camped)<br>
